# Mobile Performance Rules

See `docs/PERFORMANCE.md` for full context and root cause analysis.

## Banned Patterns

- **`backdrop-blur`** on any mobile-visible element → use solid `bg-white`
- **`transition-all`** → list exact properties: `transition-[color,background-color,opacity,transform]`
- **Animating `left`, `top`, `width`, `height`** → use `transform` (`translateX`, `translateY`, `scale`)
- **`document.body.style.overflow = "hidden"`** → use `position: fixed` + `top: -scrollY` pattern
- **Double `requestAnimationFrame`** → single RAF unless provably required
- **Duplicate stateful components** → never mount two instances of a component with hooks

## StickySearchBar (HomePageClient.tsx)

There must be exactly ONE `<StickySearchBar>` instance. It uses `hero` and `visible` props to switch presentation. Never add a second instance.

```tsx
// ✅ Single instance passed via render prop
<HeroSection searchBar={<StickySearchBar hero={!showSticky} visible={showSticky} />} />

// ❌ NEVER do this — two instances = ~40 hooks, double React work
<StickySearchBar hero />          {/* inside HeroSection */}
<StickySearchBar visible={show} /> {/* at root level */}
```

## SiteHeader Hamburger Menu

Body scroll lock must use `position: fixed` pattern:

```tsx
// ✅ iOS-safe scroll lock
document.body.style.position = "fixed";
document.body.style.top = `-${scrollY}px`;
// On close: restore position and scrollTo(0, savedScrollY)

// ❌ Triggers iOS layout reflow
document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
```

## Heavy Imports

Import `maplibre-gl/dist/maplibre-gl.css` only in `MapPreview.tsx` (lazy-loaded), never in root layout.
